men,” have posted closing notices. And several others have been pushed into the fall, such as the musicals “Caroline, or Change” and “Flying Over Sunset.” New York Post Vanguard The 2020 Skysports newspapers awards and logo unveiling billed for March 25 in Benin City, Edo State has been put off due to coronavirus concerns. According to the organisers the event which was scheduled to highlight the Edo 2020 Sports Festival, will get a new date when the coronavirus clouds… March 22, 2020 In "Sports" The sporting world has not been spared by the rampaging COVID-19 virus, with players, managers and officials falling victim to the virus all over the world. In a bid to curtail the spread of the virus, several sports governing bodies have made decisions ranging from postponement to outright cancellation of… March 14, 2020 In "Sports" Comedian I Go Dye has postponed his show tagged “I Go Dye Standing, "Kinging with the Kings" to commemorate his 25 years on stage over the spread of Coronavirus across the globe. March 18, 2020 In "Entertainment"